5\">{{cite web | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/books/romance-finally-breaks-the-posts-no-self-published-books-rule/2015/11/24/984636fe-9259-11e5-a2d6-f57908580b1f_story.html | title=Romance finally breaks The Post's 'No Self-Published Books' rule | publisher=WashPost | date=26 November 2015 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Ron Charles | quote=\".... I think this new open market can \u2013 and does \u2013 make for much more interesting storytelling\u2026.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsWashPost0909\">{{cite web | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2014/10/01/no-i-dont-want-to-read-your-self-published-book/?tid=a_inl | title=No, I don't want to read your self-published book | work=Washington Post | date=1 October 2014 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Ron Charles | quote=\"......1. There are too many of you....\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNPR1123\">{{cite web | url=https://www.npr.org/2015/09/19/441459103/when-it-comes-to-book-sales-what-counts-as-success-might-surprise-you | title=When It Comes To Book Sales, What Counts As Success Might Surprise You | publisher=NPR | date=19 September 2015 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Lynn Neary | quote=\"...You used to be able to make an absolutely living wage as a writer. \u2026 it didn't usually mean you would be rich, but it had meant in the past that you could support yourself\u2026.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsBloomberg433\">{{cite web | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-05-26/it-s-a-writer-s-market | title=It's a Writer's Market: Digital platforms have emerged to serve midlist authors. | publisher=Bloomberg | date=26 May 2016 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Karen Angel | quote=\"...or Greg White \u2026  \"Five years ago, self-publishing was a scar,\" White says. \"Now it's a tattoo.\"...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNYT9897\">{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/01/us/young-writers-find-a-devoted-publisher-thanks-mom-and-dad.html | ti