c.com/entertainment/archive/2016/06/plagiarism-in-the-age-of-self-publishing/485525/ Stealing Books in the Age of Self-Publishing: Many authors who sell their work directly on platforms like Amazon are having their stories plagiarized, which can take an emotional and financial toll.], Retrieved 31 October 2017, \"...Rachel Ann Nunes ... First published in 1998, A Bid for Love did well enough to spawn two sequels ... Mullens' book, titled The Auction Deal, looked like the same story with much of the same language...\"</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsRI1010\">{{cite web | url=https://www.researchinformation.info/news/self-publishing-isbns-rise | title=Self-publishing ISBNs on the rise | publisher=Research information | date=12 October 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | quote=\"...International Standard Book Numbers (ISBNs) for self-published titles have climbed 218.33 per cent since 2011, according to the latest report from ProQuest affiliate Bowker\u2026\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsBauer\">{{cite web | url=http://lmtribune.com/a_and_e/publishing-glad-tidings/article_b86c0215-73ee-5f75-b132-cbfd60846f46.html | title=Publishing? Glad tidings: Aspiring writers, take note: Library is holding Indie Author Day | publisher=Lewiston Tribune | date=12 October 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Jennifer K. Bauer | quote=\".. free self-publishing platform called Self-e, a collaboration between Library Journal and BiblioBoard \u2026. more of a marketing tool.\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsPW4342\">{{cite web | url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/industry-news/manufacturing/article/75139-self-published-isbns-hit-786-935-in-2016.html | title=Self-Published ISBNs Hit 786,935 in 2016 | publisher=Publishers Weekly | date=20 October 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Jim Milliot | quote=\"...Since Bowker measures the number of self-published books by ISBN, its count does not include e-books released by authors through Amazon's KDP program ... they use ASIN identifiers rather than an ISBNs....\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsQuartz101\">{{cite web | url=https://qz.com/1077996/self-publishing-on-amazon-amzn-how-an-author-can-hack-a-books-success-sales-and-royalties/ | title=Amazon has laid out exactly how to game its self-publishing platform | publisher=Quartz media | date=20 September 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Thu-Huong Ha | quote=\"\u2026 Amazon established its collective fund for self-published books, last month's US pot, at $19.4 million, \u2026  authors got the second lowest payout ever ... at $0.00419 per page read...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNYT43432\">{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/10/style/romance-novels-diversity.html?_r=0 | title=In Love With Romance Novels, but Not Their Lack of Diversity | work=The New York Times | date=10 October 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=KATHERINE ROSMAN | quote=\"... best-selling romance author who has turned to self-publishing in order to have more agency over the background of her characters \u2026  systemic problem in that publishing is insular \u2026 nobody understood \u2026 that people of color have inner lives \u2026\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsTime101\">{{cite web | url=http://time.com/3611036/photographers-become-publishers/ | title=When Photographers Become Self-Publishing Companies: An increasing number of photographers are bypassing traditional photo book publishers, setting up, instead, their own imprints | publisher=Time magazine | date=4 December 2014 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Laurence Butet-Roch | quote=\"... Investing in a project shows that you believe in it....}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNPR4432\">{{cite web | url=https://www.npr.org/2012/12/19/167448748/self-publishing-no-longer-just-a-vanity-project | title=Self-Publishing: No Longer Just A Vanity Project | publisher=NPR | date=19 December 2012 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=LYNN NEARY | quote=\"...They used to call it the \"vanity press,\" and the phrase itself spoke volumes\u2026.\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsBruno101\">{{cite web | url=http://time.com/4040880/guide-self-publish-photobook/ | title=A Manifesto to Self-Publishing Your Own Photobooks | publisher=Time magazine | date=21 September 2015 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Bruno Ceschel | quote=\"...\"The act of self publishing has a longstanding roots, from the very beginning of the history of book making,\" adds Ceschel. \"It has always been an act of defiance against oppression (religious, political, economic, sexual, etc). DIY culture is, by its nature, an ethic in opposition to society's rules at large. It flourishes in environments of communitarian support, collaboration, and even informal barter economies.\"...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsUSAToday143\">{{cite web | url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2013/11/29/the-upsurge-in-self-published-books/3191731/ | title=Companies book profits from self-publishing | publisher=USA Today | date=29 November 2013 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Jeremy Greenfield | quote=\"\u2026 According to Smashwords \u2026  the best-selling 1% of titles net half the sales\u2026.\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsSlatemag1\">{{cite web | url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2017/06/06/milo_yiannopoulos_self_published_book_topped_amazon_s_best_seller_list.html | title=Milo Yiannopoulos' Self-Published Book Is an Amazon Best-Seller. So Much for Free-Speech Martyrdom. | publisher=Slate magazine | date=6 June 2017 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Marissa Martinelli | quote=\"... While Simon & Schuster had previously defended the decision to publish Yiannopoulos' book \u2026 the publisher finally dropped the British provocateur...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNPR2322\">{{cite web | url=https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2014/07/25/334484331/unknown-authors-make-a-living-self-publishing | title=Self-Published Authors Make A Living \u2013 And Sometimes A Fortune | publisher=NPR | date=25 July 2014 | accessdate=2