\">{{cite web | url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/penguin-random-house-sells-self-publishing-company-1452025422 | title=Penguin Random House Sells Self-Publishing Company: Affiliate of Najafi Cos., a private-equity firm, buys Author Solutions | publisher=WSJ | date=5 January 2016 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=Jeffrey A. Trachtenberg | quote=\"...Penguin Random House has sold self-publishing company Author Solutions \u2026 Penguin Group had acquired Author Solutions \u2026 in 2012 for $116 million...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNPR899\">{{cite web | url=https://www.npr.org/2013/02/04/171103053/self-publishing-now-the-first-choice-for-some-writers | title=Self-Publishing Now The First Choice For Some Writers | publisher=NPR | date=4 February 2013 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=All Things Considered; Robert Siegel (host); Audie Cornish (host) | quote=\"....survey found that the number of self-published books in the U.S. has almost tripled in the past six years\u2026.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsNYT4221\">{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/22/books/review/the-case-for-self-publishing.html | title=The Case for Self-Publishing | publisher=NYT | date=20 May 2011 | accessdate=20 October 2017 | author=NEAL POLLACK | quote=\"...  midcareer, midlist, middle-aged, more or less middlebrow, and somewhat Internet savvy \u2013 self-publishing seems to make a lot of sense \u2026 why not start appealing directly to those readers?...\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsFortune147\">Jennifer Alsever, Fortune magazine, 30 December 2016, [http://fortune.com/2016/12/30/amazon-kindle-digital-self-publishing/ The Kindle Effect], Retrieved 9 November 2017, \"...has become a $1 billion industry...\"</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"twsFortune148\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/eshachhabra/2017/08/31/london-startup-uses-technology-to-open-up-the-world-of-book-publishing/#6559e26e6197|title=London Startup Uses Technology To Open Up The World of Book Publishing|last=Chhabra|