were a state, but not more than the least populous state. This has always been three.''\n: ** ''Maine's four electors and Nebraska's five are distributed using the [[#Congressional district method|Congressional district method]].''\n\n== Chronological table ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:80%;line-height:1.1;\"\n|+ <big><big>Number of presidential electors by state and year</big></big>\n|- valign=bottom\n! colspan=2 rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:right\" | Election<br />year\n! colspan=3  | 1788\u20131800\n! colspan=18 | 1804\u20131900\n! colspan=11 | 1904\u20132000\n! colspan=2  | 2004\u2013\n|- valign=bottom\n! [[1788\u201389 United States presidential election|'88]]\n! [[1792 United States presidential election|'92]]\n! [[1796 United States presidential election|'96]]<br />[[1800 United States presidential election|'00]]\n! [[1804 United States presidential election|'04]]<br />[[1808 United States presidential election|'08]]\n! [[1812 United States presidential election|'12]]\n! [[1816 United States presidential election|'16]]\n! [[1820 United States presidential election|'20]]\n! [[1824 United States presidential election|'24]]<br />[[1828 United States presidential election|'28]]\n! [[1832 United States presidential election|'32]]\n! [[1836 United States presidential election|'36]]<br />[[1840 United States presidential election|'40]]\n! [[1844 United States presidential election|'44]]\n! [[1848 United States presidential election|'48]]\n! [[1852 United States presidential election|'52]]<br />[[1856 United States presidential election|'56]]\n! [[1860 United States presidential election|'60]]\n! [[1864 United States presidential election|'64]]<!--\n   NOTE REGARDING SORTING FOR 1864\u201368 ELECTIONS\n   The southern states are shown as an explicit '0' between secession and restoration of representation in Congress.\n   In order to sort these separately from the {{not polled}} states not yet admitted, an explicit sort key is used.\n   This apparently disrupts the automatic recognition of numeric sorting.\n   This is fixed by adding a hidden leading zero in the sort key for single-digit entries in 1864.\n   No sort key is needed for double-digit entries.\n   I would expect the same problem to occur in 1868 when three states are not yet restored.\n   However, it does not seem to be necessary, probably because Alabama (first in alpha order) was already restored.\n   It seems possible that this fix may not work on all browsers.\n   If further problems are noted, ping me on the talk page and I'll have another look at it.\n   --- YBG, 2016-03-01\n-->\n! [[1868 United States presidential election|'68]]\n! [[1872 United States presidential election|'72]]\n! [[1876 United States presidential election|'76]]<br />[[1880 United States presidential election|'80]]\n! [[1884 United States presidential election|'84]]<br />[[1888 United States presidential election|'88]]\n! [[1892 United States presidential election|'92]]\n! [[1896 United States presidential election|'96]]<br />[[1900 United States presidential election|'00]]\n! [[1904 United States presidential election|'04]]\n! [[1908 United States presidential election|'08]]\n! [[1912 United States presidential election|'12]]<br />[[1916 United States presidential election|'16]]<br />[[1920 United States presidential election|'20]]<br />[[1924 United States presidential election|'24]]<br />[[1928 United States presidential election|'28]]\n! [[1932 United States presidential election|'32]]<br />[[1936 United States presidential election|'36]]<br />[[1940 United States presidential election|'40]]\n! [[1944 United States presidential election|'44]]<br />[[1948 United States presidential election|'48]]\n! [[1952 United States presidential election|'52]]<br />[[1956 United States presidential election|'56]]\n! [[1960 United States presidential election|'60]]\n! [[1964 United States presidential election|'64]]<br />[[1968 United States presidential elect