n male soap opera actors]] \n[[Category:People from Agra]] \n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi television]] \n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]  \n[[Category:1989 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=August 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Pearl V Puri\n| image              = Handsome Pearl V Puri Clicked by Sajid Shahid (42093188620) (cropped).jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1989|7|10}}<ref name=\"IT Puri DOB\" />\n| birth_place        = [[Chhindwara]], [[Madhya Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = Indian \n| occupation         = Actor \n| yearsactive        = 2013\u2013present\n}}\n'''Pearl V Puri''' (born 10 July 1989)<ref name=\"IT Puri DOB\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/television/celebrity/story/naagin-3-team-reunited-to-celebrate-pearl-v-puri-s-birthday-see-pics-and-videos-1565943-2019-07-10|title=Naagin 3 team reunited to celebrate Pearl V Puri's birthday. See pics and videos|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-10-13}}</ref> is an Indian television actor known for his work in ''[[Naagin (2015 TV series)|Naagin 3]].\n\n==Career==\nPuri made his debut in 2013 with ''[[Dil Ki Nazar Se Khoobsurat]]''.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/television/celebrities/vs-now-pearl-v-puri-looked-riding-top/2019/09/17|title=THIS is how Pearl V Puri looked before riding on top|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2015, he appeared in ''[[Phir Bhi Na Maane...Badtameez Dil]]''.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Snakes-on-the-set-of-Pearls-TV-show/articleshow/47973763.cms?from=mdr|title=Snakes on the set of Pearl\u2019s TV show}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Pearl-Puri-Gujaratis-are-extremely-helpful/articleshow/47975097.cms?from=mdr|title=Pearl Puri: Gujaratis are extremely helpful}}</ref> In 2016, he had roles in ''[[Meri Saasu Ma]]'' and  ''[[Naagarjuna - Ek Yoddha]]''.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\nFrom 2018 to 2019, Puri played Mahir Sehgal and Mihir Sippi in ''[[Naagin (2015 TV series)|Naagin 3]]'' opposite [[Surbhi Jyoti]].<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/naagin-3-actor-pearl-v-puri-i-believe-naagins-exist-5274726/|title=I believe naagins exist: Naagin 3 actor Pearl V Puri|date=2018-07-25|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=2019-05-05}}</ref> From 2019 to 2020, he portrayed Raghbir Malhotra in ''[[Bepanah Pyaar]]'' opposite [[Aparna Dixit]] and [[Ishita Dutta]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n==Media==\nIn 2018, Puri was ranked first in ''[[Times of India]]''{{'}}s Most Desirable Men on TV List.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/telly-talk/gossip/article/naagin-3-actor-pearl-v-puri-takes-the-top-spot-in-the-times-20-most-desirable-men-of-tv-2018-list/416827|title=Naagin 3 actor Pearl V Puri takes the top spot in The Times 20 Most Desirable Men of TV 2018 list|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He was also ranked 26th in The 50 Most Desirable Men List.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vicky-kaushal-is-the-times-most-desirable-man-of-2018/articleshow/69361561.cms|title=Pearl V Puri grabbed at 26th spot among the times most desirable dudes of 2018|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He was ranked 20th in the 2019 TV Personality List by ''Biz Asia.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizasialive.com/tv-personality-2019-live-updates/|title=TV Personality 2019: Live updates|last=#|date=2019-12-25|website=BizAsia {{!}} Media, Entertainment, Showbiz, Brit, Events and Music|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\